The Coalition of Civil Society for Citizen’s Action Against COVID-19 has lauded the National Broadcasting Commission’s (NBC) ongoing reform in the broadcasting sector aimed at protecting local operators, promoting creativity and maximizing local contents. Recall that the Commission recently approved a new broadcasting code, tagged:  The 6th edition of the Nigerian Broadcasting Code which all broadcasting stations had been advised to comply with. A statement signed by the national coordinator of the coalition, Amb Splendour Agbonkpolor, and made available to LEADERSHIP yesterday in Abuja, advocated for more engagements by stakeholders in the implementation of the new code which seeks to give the Nigerian government more control over broadcasting platforms not yet under government control like internet, TV and radio. He said the coalition having read some of the strong and salient oppositions from some concerned stakeholders on some sections of the code that tend to break the monopoly currently enjoyed by some foreign broadcasting organisations, called on NBC to organise a forum for stakeholders to make recommendations to strengthen the code so that it won’t frustrate the ongoing investments in the broadcasting sector. The statement reads in part: “The NBC new code makes it mandatory for broadcast media to ensure that 70 per cent of their productions are local contents base, thereby creating an avenue to stimulate local investors in the content development sector and giving more opportunities to local producers and film makers. This is a welcome development and a big investment opportunity to Nollywood “With the advent of digital technology, the broadcasting sector has been undergoing significant technological and structural changes which have given Nigerian’ consumers access to a great variety of communications and media services. “This new code should push the full implementation of the much talked about Digital Switch Over and stimulate citizen’s response and participation in broadcasting.” He, however, called on NBC to ensure that the broadcast stations takes into consideration the economic, social, cultural or technical nature of the nation and ensure that the contents should be directed towards promoting these sectors.